originalText.text:
Gatsby's Landing offers a nice decor suggestive of high-end dining along with acceptable service which is uneven at best.  The food presentation was good and the taste overall was satisfying and good.

An important note that the restaurant does NOT tell you until your bill arrives is they place an extra charge for using anything but cash to pay.  Yes, there are a number of restaurants that do this, but in this day and age when the restaurant technology that is utilized is based on electronics they should either roll that costs into the menu prices.  Our waiter sent over a manager who stated he understood, his hands were tied, and it was the restaurant owner who has directed this method of charging.  We explained that it is our decision where to spend our food dollar(s), and our decision would be to never return.   We would suggest if this is the business model the restaurant wishes to use, they should post this on their website and prominently on the menu -- not a surprise at the end of the meal.

Some of the issues observed was that the person bussing the table took our fork from the salad bowl and placed it on the table for the next course, yet the waiter when removing another appetizer dish replace that individual's fork -- inconsistent service style.  Delivery of food but not knowing which dish went to which person.  Overall, the food taste was good but certainly would not consider the meals exceptional.

This party of 5 will not be returning for a comparison meal which is sad because one visit is not always enough, but as mentioned the business model is not where we would spend our food dollar.

Hope you have a better experience.

If I could've given 10 stars in all the categories for this restaurant, I would've.

We L.O.V.E.D EVERYTHING!!!!

Our waiter, Greg was so informed, so fun, so friendly and just so welcoming and... I don't know... everything he should've been. He was perfect.

The food!!
Three of us dined... we were celebrating two birthdays... ordered different drinks, different meals... all had our eyeballs rolling to the back of our heads it was so good.

Beautiful atmosphere... just top notch all the way around.

Go Go Go Go.

If you're reading this trying to decide between places for dinner... your search is over.
Absolutely Go!

originalText.text: My partner and I came here to celebrate one of our birthdays. This place did not disappoint. From the moment you walk into the front door, you are greeted with professionalism. We were escorted to our seats and were actually told to choose wherever we wanted to sit. The entire area was secluded. So we had a whole section all to ourselves.Which was lovely. Our waiter, named Lauren, who is fairly new working for the establishment, was great!  She conversated with us and explained everything on the menu to us.  We started off with Calamari as our appetizer. As entrées we got a Burger entree and a salmon entree. Both were very tasty.  This restaurant is definitely not just somewhere to get a quick bite to eat. It's somewhere where you want to sit and relax and pay good money, for some good food. I would definitely recommend someone come here to eat. The atmosphere is very dim and romantic.It gives a very calm vibe.
